						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/The-Cotonou-Agreement-A-User-s-Guide" title="The Cotonou Agreement: A User's Guide" alt="link">The Cotonou Agreement: A User's Guide</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>Commonwealth Secretariat, 9 December 2004</i>. This new publication uses a question and answer format to simplify the Cotonou Agreement, so as to maximise the benefits for people in ACP countries. The guide is divided into four parts. Part 1 provides a general introduction to the structure of the Cotonou Agreement and explains where its various provisions can be found. Part 2 looks at the financial and technical cooperation agreements and reviews basic provisions for the involvement of non-state actors and the private sector. Part 3 examines trade arrangements under the agreement, while part 4 deals with political relations within the framework of the accord. The areas covered include the scope of political dialogue; the principles underpinning the ACP?EU relationship; the commitments entered into through endorsement of these principles; and commitments on peace-building, conflict prevention and conflict resolution.</p>
							<p><span class="date">22/12/2004</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/The-Cotonou-Agreement-A-User-s-Guide">Read more...</a>
