						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Global-Knowledge-a-research-magazine" title="Global Knowledge (a research magazine)" alt="link">Global Knowledge (a research magazine)</a></h2>

	
					<p> <i>Global Knowledge</i> is a new magazine focused on cooperation in research and higher education between Norway and countries in the South and East. Research and theories developed in and aimed at Western societies may not necessarily function if they are directly transferred to countries in other parts of the world. The aim of the interdisciplinary magazine is to present research that has had a positive impact on societies as well as individuals, and to create a forum for debate. The first issue focuses on democracy, with articles about or from Burkina Faso, Ghana, Malawi, South Africa, Uganda, Zambia, and many other countries.</p>
							<p><span class="date">7/01/2005</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Selected-publications/Global-Knowledge-a-research-magazine">Read more...</a>
